detail_description: Paraty, a charming colonial town located in Rio de Janeiro State, is situated about 250 km south of Rio de Janeiro city. The town boasts breathtaking scenery, a relaxed atmosphere, excellent dining options, and a rich historical heritage. Paraty is a popular weekend destination for residents of Rio and Sao Paolo due to its alluring qualities. The cobblestone streets adorned with colorful doors and flowers create a picturesque setting that exudes an enchanting ambiance.
name: Paraty
address: State of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil

excerpt: Paraty is a small town backed by mountains on Brazil's Costa Verde, between Rio de Janeiro and São Paulo. Its Portuguese colonial center has cobbled streets and 17th- and 18th-century buildings dating to its time as a port, during the Brazilian Gold Rush. Among its architectural landmarks is the waterfront Capela de Santa Rita, a whitewashed church built in 1722.
detail_description: Paraty, a charming town nestled amidst the mountains of Brazil's Costa Verde, boasts a well-preserved Portuguese colonial center with cobblestone streets and centuries-old buildings dating back to its days as a bustling port during the Brazilian Gold Rush. One of its architectural gems is the Capela de Santa Rita, an elegant whitewashed church constructed in 1722. The town also offers a rich cultural experience with exhibits showcasing historical and iconographic information, providing insight into local rituals and traditions.
name: Paraty
address: State of Rio de Janeiro, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: Trindade is a charming beach village located on the border of Rio de Janeiro and Sao Paulo, making it a popular destination for travelers exploring the stunning Costa Verde region. The area offers a variety of beautiful beaches, including both commercial spots with seaside cafes and more secluded shores accessible via scenic trails. Trindade is known for its laid-back, hippie vibe and excellent dining options.
name: Trindade
address: Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

excerpt: Conserved colonial enclave & former gold mining port with cobbled streets, churches & forts.
detail_description: Paraty, a charming coastal city in Brazil, is a beautifully preserved colonial enclave that once thrived as a gold mining port. With its cobbled streets and historic churches, the town exudes an enchanting atmosphere. Visitors are greeted by the serene absence of cars, allowing for peaceful exploration amidst stunning natural surroundings of lush mountains and tranquil waters. The city's commitment to maintaining this calm environment enhances the experience for travelers seeking relaxation and adventure alike.
name: Paraty
address: R. Ten. Francisco Antonio - Centro Histórico, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

excerpt: A steep trail leads to this flat-topped peak for far-reaching views of the tropical fjord below.
detail_description: Sugarloaf Peak (Mamanguá) is a flat-topped peak with stunning views of the tropical fjord below. Visitors can enjoy various activities such as kayaking to deserted beaches, hiking up the peak for impressive views, and exploring the mangrove in canoes. The area also offers opportunities to join the local caicaras for lunch and take private boat tours from Mamangua to Paraty, stopping at islands and isolated beaches along the way.
name: Sugarloaf Peak (Mamanguá)
address: Saco do Mamangua, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: Casa da Cultura de Paraty, also known as the House of Culture, is a must-visit in the town's historic center. Housed in an 18th-century mansion, this museum offers a comprehensive look at Paraty's history and cultural heritage through photos, artifacts, and personal accounts from residents throughout the ages. The well-curated exhibits beautifully represent the region's cultural and natural heritage. Additionally, visitors can enjoy a friendly café and various cultural activities on-site.
name: Casa da Cultura de Paraty
address: R. Dona Geralda, 194 - Centro Histórico, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: Cachoeira do Tobogã, located a short drive away from Paraty, is a unique waterfall where the water flows over a stone to form a natural slide and pool. To reach this attraction, visitors can take a bus from Rodoviaria de Paraty to the neighborhood of Penha. The highlight of the place is the surfing stone that adds an element of entertainment for both locals and tourists.
name: Cachoeira do Tobogã
address: Rod. Parati - Cunha, km8 - Penha, Paraty - RJ, 23970-970, Brazil

detail_description: Paraty Bay is a picturesque destination set against the backdrop of a lush coastal mountain range. With over 50 islands and 100 beaches, it offers plenty of opportunities for exploration in its protected waters. The area also boasts tropical mangroves, historic ruins, and fishing villages that showcase the region's biodiversity and culture, earning it recognition from UNESCO. Additionally, Paraty Bay has a rich history as an exit point for treasures bound for Portugal and as a stronghold for corsairs and pirates.
name: Paraty Bay
address: Paraty, RJ, Brazil

excerpt: Happening beach with on-site bars & restaurants, rentable lounge chairs & swimming.
detail_description: Praia dos Ranchos, also known as Praia de Fora, is a happening beach located about 25km south of Paraty in Trindade. This stunning coastline offers four dazzling beaches with surging breakers, enormous boulders, and vast expanses of mountain-fringed white sand. Visitors can enjoy on-site bars and restaurants right on the sand, rentable lounge chairs for relaxation, and swimming in the calm waters.
name: Praia dos Ranchos
address: Trindade, Rio de Janeiro, Paraty - State of Rio de Janeiro, 23970-000, Brazil

excerpt: Bustling tree-lined stretch of coastline featuring numerous food & drink vendors.
detail_description: Praia do Pontal is a bustling tree-lined stretch of coastline with numerous food and drink vendors. It's the closest beach to the historical center of Paraty, offering a laid-back atmosphere where visitors can relax with a cold beer or traditional Brazilian caipirinha from beach bars. The beach also provides opportunities for sea kayaking, paddle-boarding, and boat rentals.
name: Praia do Pontal
address: Av. Orlando Carpinelli, 4 - Pontal, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

excerpt: Small boats access this secluded locale with a tranquil, white-sand beach & hiking trails.
detail_description: Praia do Sono is a secluded and tranquil beach accessible by small boats, located near the coastal village of Trindade. It is renowned for its pristine white sands, calm and clear waters perfect for swimming, and hiking trails through rough jungle paths. The area offers simple guest houses and a few families living in the vicinity who work in local restaurants and bars.
name: Praia do Sono
address: State of Rio de Janeiro, 23970-000, Brazil

excerpt: Traditional recipes from coastal Brazil, served in an elegant colonial villa with garden tables.
detail_description: Restaurante Banana da Terra is a renowned dining spot in Paraty, offering traditional coastal Brazilian dishes in an elegant colonial villa with charming garden tables. The restaurant is known for its fresh-caught local fish and shrimp, making it a top choice for seafood enthusiasts. For those seeking a unique experience, the Academy of Cooking and Other Pleasures hosted by Brazilian chef Yara Castro Roberts and her husband Richard Roberts offers dinner events combined with cooking classes.
name: Restaurante Banana da Terra
address: R. Dr. Samuel Costa, 198 - Centro Histórico, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

excerpt: Across the river from the historic center, Pontal is home to the Praia do Pontal, a popular beach lined with laid-back bars and kiosks serving local fish and shrimp dishes. Kayaks and standup paddleboards can be rented for Paraty Bay. A steep trail leads to the Forte Defensor Perpétuo, dating to 1703, with sweeping views and antique cannons. Inland, homey Brazilian restaurants cater to local families and backpackers.
detail_description: Located across the river from Paraty's historic center, Pontal is a vibrant area known for Praia do Pontal, a popular beach with relaxed bars and kiosks offering local seafood. Visitors can rent kayaks and standup paddleboards to explore Paraty Bay. A steep trail leads to Forte Defensor Perpétuo, an ancient fortress dating back to 1703, providing stunning views and featuring old cannons.
name: Pontal
address: Paraty - State of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil

detail_description: Paraty Sport Aventura is the largest arvorism park in Brazil, offering circuits for both adults and children, as well as activities such as zip-lining, rappelling, kayaking, and picnicking. The park is located near the Rio-Santos highway in Paraty and offers canyoning trips. Visitors have praised the entertaining experience and recommended trying the red circuit and zip line.
name: Paraty Sport Aventura
address: Rod. Br-101 Rio Santos, Km 575 - Zona Rural, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

excerpt: 1822 museum set in a former battery featuring 18th-century cannons, plus hiking trails & bay views.
detail_description: Museu Forte Defensor Perpétuo is a historical site located in Paraty, offering visitors a glimpse into the 18th-century defensive history of the region. The former battery features well-preserved cannons and provides stunning views of the bay. A short hike through bamboo forests leads to the fort, where a small museum showcases its history.
name: Museu Forte Defensor Perpétuo
address: Av. Orlando Carpinelli, 440 - Pontal, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: Paraty Mirim is a spacious beach with a length of 760 meters, offering tranquil waters and divided by the Paraty-Mirim river. The area features two or three kiosks for visitors to enjoy refreshments. Both the beach and the nearby village share the name Paraty-Mirim, creating a charming connection between the coastal landscape and local community.
name: Paraty Mirim
address: Paraty-Mirim, Paraty - State of Rio de Janeiro, 23970-000, Brazil

excerpt: Full of hostels and pousadas, compact Jabaquara is known for the beach of the same name, popular for kayaking and standup paddleboarding in calm Paraty Bay. Casual beachfront restaurants and seafood kiosks, many with tree-shaded seating, serve local fish and shrimp specialties. A cycling path hugs the coast, and the mud in the mangrove area at the northern end of the beach is said to have healing properties.
detail_description: Jabaquara is a charming area known for its compact size and abundance of hostels and pousadas. The beach, after which the neighborhood is named, is a popular spot for kayaking and standup paddleboarding in the calm waters of Paraty Bay. Visitors can enjoy casual beachfront restaurants serving local fish and shrimp specialties, many offering shaded seating.
name: Jabaquara
address: Paraty - State of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil

detail_description: Cachoeira Saco Bravo is a hidden gem in Brazil, accessible through a two-day trekking tour or as part of the five-day 'Volta da Joatinga' tour. The journey takes you off the beaten path, along jungle trails, dream beaches, waterfalls, and charming fishing communities like Ponta Negra and Cajaiba. Accommodation options include camping or staying in local guest rooms with delicious fish dishes on offer.
name: Cachoeira Saco Bravo
address: Paraty-Mirim, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: The Circuit Gold Trail offers a unique alternative to the typical Paraty hiking experience, as it does not lead to the beach. This historic trail was originally constructed by slaves and served as a vital connection between Paraty and the gold-rich state of Minas Gerais in Brazil's countryside. As part of a restoration effort, 5km of this ancient highway has been reconstructed for modern exploration.
name: Circuit Gold Trail
address: Rodovia RJ-165, Km 11 s/n Zona Rural, Paraty - RJ, 12530-000, Brazil

detail_description: Praia de São Gonçalo is a popular destination for tourists, featuring a long beach that can be accessed by crossing a small river either on foot or by canoe, depending on the tide. Visitors can also take boats from the beach to Ilha dos Pelados, which is known for its bars. It's an ideal spot to relax and enjoy cold drinks while taking in the beautiful surroundings. This beach offers a tranquil escape and is highly recommended for those seeking a peaceful getaway in Paraty.
name: Praia de São Gonçalo
address: Tarituba, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: Praça da Matriz is home to the grand Igreja da Matriz, Paraty's largest and most elaborate church. The church has a rich history, evolving from a small chapel in 1646 to its current neoclassical form completed in 1873. Adjacent to the square is Casa da Cultura, originally constructed as a private residence and warehouse in 1754.
name: Praça da Matriz
address: Centro Histórico, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: Embark on an unforgettable adventure along the Trilha Saco do Mamanguá, a captivating journey that leads you through the lush landscapes of Angra dos Reis. This trail offers a thrilling challenge with its steep ascent, rewarding hikers with breathtaking views of the surrounding forest and mountains. The trek typically takes around 1 hour and 20 minutes round trip, so be sure to pack water and snacks to keep your energy up!
name: Trilha Saco do Mamanguá
address: Saco de Managuá - Paraty-Mirim, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: Caminho do Ouro, also known as the Gold Trail, gained prominence in the 17th century when Portuguese missionaries and gold miners established Paraty and its surrounding area. The region's significance waned by the late 18th century after the depletion of gold reserves and completion of missionary work. However, a revival occurred with the rise of coffee and cachaca trade. It wasn't until the 1970s that Caminho do Ouro began to attract significant attention from tourists.
name: Caminho do ouro
address: RJ-165 - Paraty, RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: The Walkingtour Center Historic Paraty is a wonderful place that offers a unique experience for visitors. With its charming cobblestone streets, well-preserved colonial architecture, and rich history, it's a must-visit destination for anyone interested in immersing themselves in the cultural heritage of the region. The guided walking tour provides insightful commentary on the significance of various landmarks and allows you to appreciate the beauty of this historic area at a leisurely pace.
name: Walkingtour center historic paraty
address: Centro Histórico, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

excerpt: Long, wide beach with a trail to natural pools surrounded by rocks & preserved native vegetation.
detail_description: Cachadaço beach is a stunning, wide stretch of coastline with a trail leading to natural pools surrounded by rocks and lush native vegetation. To reach this tropical paradise, travelers can take a paved road from Bairro do Patrimonio in Paraty or pay attention after crossing the border between Sao Paulo and Rio de Janeiro when coming from Ubatuba to Trindade. The beach is a favorite among explorers for its access to the Atlantic Forest hillside and short trail.

address: Trindade, Rio de Janeiro, State of Rio de Janeiro, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: The hiking trail to Cachadaço Natural Pool in Trindade Village offers a serene and clean natural swimming experience among colorful fishes. The medium difficulty trail is well-marked with steps, handrails, and boardwalks over swampy areas. Accessible from the beach, the 30-minute walk is suitable for most visitors, although closed-toe shoes are recommended. For those seeking an alternative to the trail, boat transport is available for a fee.

address: Brazil

detail_description: Pedra da Praia do Meio is a stunning beach located in Trindade, Brazil. It offers the opportunity to take leisurely walks along the sand and explore hiking trails leading to attractions like Piscina Natural do Caixadaco. Visitors can also opt for a speed boat from Praia do Meio if they prefer not to hike. The beach is known for its tranquil atmosphere and natural beauty, making it a must-visit destination in the area.
name: Pedra da Praia do Meio
address: Trindade, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: Lula Beach, also known as Praia da Lulu or Beach of the Squid, is a secluded gem located on a small uninhabited island near Paraty. Accessible only by sea, this beautiful sandy beach boasts crystal clear waters and pristine white sands. The surrounding ocean is warm and inviting, perfect for swimming and relaxation. Visitors can enjoy the tranquil atmosphere and natural beauty of the inland forest that extends to the edge of the shore.
name: Lula Beach
address: Paraty, State of Rio de Janeiro, 23970-000, Brazil

excerpt: River rock feature where adventurous bathers slide through a hole & into a pool on the other side.
detail_description: Located in the protected reserve of Cairucu, Pedra que Engole offers an adventurous experience for visitors. This natural rock formation features a hole through which bathers can slide into a pool on the other side. The trail to reach this hidden gem is indicated by signs and takes you through a tropical forest along a river. The experience includes sliding through the water and enjoying a natural pool nestled between rocks.
name: Pedra que Engole

detail_description: Praia da Ilha Pelada is a stunning destination with three beautiful beaches, clear sand, and warm, crystal-clear waters. Accessible only by boat, this paradise offers a serene escape from the hustle and bustle of city life. Visitors can enjoy a leisurely day at the beach and indulge in delicious meals at the island's restaurant. With its natural beauty and tranquil atmosphere, Praia da Ilha Pelada is an ideal spot for nature enthusiasts seeking an unforgettable coastal experience.
name: Praia da Ilha do Pelado
address: Parque Imperial, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

excerpt: Small cachaça distillery offering guided tours with tastings & a bar, a restaurant & a gift shop.
detail_description: Alambique Engenho D'Ouro is a renowned cachaça distillery in the region, offering guided tours with tastings, a bar, restaurant, and a gift shop. The tour provides insight into the process of making Brazil's famous spirit from processing sugar cane to aging it in wooden barrels. Visitors get to sample various types of cachaça during the tour. The distillery also has an English-speaking guide who provides a comprehensive tour of the grounds.

address: Rod. Parati - Cunha, 7833 - Km 8 - Penha, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: Located in Paraty, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, Cachoeira da Pedra Branca is a stunning waterfall consisting of two natural cascades that crash into a large pool surrounded by rocks. Accessible via the road to Fazenda Murycana, it's a popular spot for swimming and relaxation. Visitors can enjoy the refreshing cool waters and even climb the stone wall for more adventurous activities.
name: Cachoeira da Pedra Branca
address: Paraty, RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: Located in Paraty, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, the Church of Our Lady of Sorrows was built in the early 19th century and was initially frequented by affluent women. Renovated a century later, it features an intriguing cemetery within its central courtyard. The church's image of Nossa Senhora da Piedade was stolen and recovered years later. Despite COVID restrictions limiting interior access, visitors appreciate its serene surroundings and picturesque colonial architecture by the riverside and sea.
name: Church of Our Lady of Sorrows
address: R. da Capela - Centro Histórico, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: Praia da Joatinga is an iconic beach located in a fashionable district of Rio de Janeiro. It has become popular on Instagram due to its impressive sunsets and stunning scenery. Although not as easily accessible as other beaches in the area, it offers a unique and private experience. The beach is situated within a condominium and offers breathtaking views, making it perfect for activities like rappelling along the cliffs. Visitors can enjoy the tranquil atmosphere and purchase refreshing coconut juice from nearby vendors.
name: Praia da Joatinga
address: Joá, Rio de Janeiro - State of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil

detail_description: Praia Sao Gonçalinho, located 32 km away, is a stunning beach known for its calm and warm green waters, making it ideal for families with children. The beach offers easy accessibility with a parking lot right in front and some shade available. Visitors can also enjoy food at the restaurant and use their umbrellas. Praia Sao Gonçalinho is much more accessible than other beaches in the area and boasts beautiful views with almost no waves.
name: Praia Sao Gonçalinho
address: Tarituba, Paraty - State of Rio de Janeiro, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: Cepilho beach in Trindade, Brazil is a special location, particularly during the early morning when the sun rises and only a few individuals traverse the stunning sands. This spot is ideal for body surfing or swimming in slightly more turbulent waters. While the entire town revolves around its beaches, it can become very crowded during summer and weekends.
name: Cepilho beach
address: Trindade, Rio de Janeiro, State of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil

detail_description: Praia de Fora is a stunning beach with clear waters and a wild, powerful vibe. It's known for its incredible views during the day and night, offering a breathtaking landscape. The left corner of the beach is perfect for capturing beautiful photos next to enormous rocks, while the sunrise here is simply mesmerizing. This beautiful place is ideal for families as it has several kiosks, bars, and restaurants nearby.
name: Praia de Fora
address: Trindade, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: When visiting Paraty, one of the must-see attractions is Poço do Tarzan. This beautiful spot features a deep well where visitors can dive from the stone and swim in its depths. There's a well-structured bar nearby with live music and even a suspension bridge to add to the charm. It's perfect for a full day of sightseeing, offering the opportunity to relax by the waterfall or take an exhilarating jump from the huge rock at the edge of the well.
name: Poço do Tarzan

detail_description: Located just a 15-minute drive inland from Paraty, Fazenda Bananal Restaurant offers a unique dining experience in an immaculately restored colonial farm setting. The restaurant serves delicious farm-to-table cuisine in a light-filled space, allowing visitors to enjoy a delightful meal before exploring the museum, tropical gardens, and working farm on the property. This simple yet evocative establishment provides insight into the area's history and future potential.
name: Fazenda Bananal Restaurant
address: Estrada da, Estr. Pedra Branca, Paraty - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

detail_description: Teatro Espaço is a small theater in Paraty that offers an amazing puppet show experience. Visitors are captivated by the six-story performance, finding it moving, impressive, and hilarious all at once. The puppets are beautifully made and act like real human beings, while the actors bring them to life with a full range of emotions and attention to detail. Meeting the director adds an extra layer of fascination and inspiration to the experience.

detail_description: Pouso da Cajaiba is a charming fishing village located in the Juatinga ecological reserve, offering a perfect escape from the hustle and bustle of Paraty. Accessible only by boat or jungle trails, this preserved beach with crystal clear waters is surrounded by picturesque fishing communities like Ponta Negra and Cajaiba. Visitors can stay overnight in simple guest rooms or tents provided by locals who also offer delicious fish dishes.
name: Pouso da Cajaiba
address: State of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil

detail_description: Antiguinho is a stunning destination located in the Cairucu Environmental Protection Area, offering fine sand and crystal-clear waters. The route to Antiguinho takes you through the Atlantic Forest, providing breathtaking views along the way. After visiting Praia do Sono and Praia de Antigos, travelers can enjoy a Caicara lunch before continuing their journey to the paradisiacal beaches of Antigos e Antiguinhos.
name: Antiguinho
address: Paraty-Mirim, Paraty - State of Rio de Janeiro, 23970-000, Brazil

excerpt: Reachable by boat, this secluded shoreline is known for its calm waters & picturesque scenery.
detail_description: Jurumirim Beach is a hidden gem that can only be accessed by boat, making it feel like your own private paradise. This stunning shoreline boasts calm waters and golden sands, all while being enveloped by the lush greenery of the Atlantic Forest. Known as the beach of renowned Brazilian explorer Amyr Klink, Jurumirim offers not just breathtaking views but also a chance to spot turtles in their natural habitat.
name: Jurumirim Beach

Built by African slaves in the early 18th century for their own use, it features gilded wooden altars and a grand chandelier inside. The church hosts lively celebrations of Sao Benedito at the beginning of December each year.

name: Praia Grande

One can even catch glimpses of the vibrant Blue Arara and Red Arara as they soar above the shoreline, creating unforgettable moments.
name: Historica Beach Village Mambucaba
address: Vila Histórica de Mambucaba, Angra dos Reis - State of Rio de Janeiro, 23900-000, Brazil

This wonderful place offers delicious water and an incredible experience for those seeking a peaceful retreat away from the crowds.
name: Ilha dos Cocos
address: Paraty-Mirim, Ilha dos Cocos - RJ, 23970-000, Brazil

excerpt: Museum housed in a 1722 stone church with historical exhibits, including many religious artifacts.
detail_description: The Museum of Sacred Art of Paraty is located in a 1722 stone church and features historical exhibits, including a collection of religious artifacts. The museum is housed in the same building as the city library and historical institute. Visitors can also explore the Forte do Defensor Perpetua, which offers stunning views of the urban area and surrounding nature. The museum offers free entry with donations welcome, making it a great place for a quick stop to admire local art and sculptures up close.

detail_description: Praia de Ponta Negra is a stunning beach located in Paraty, accessible through a route that starts near Praia do Sono and passes through the Cairucu Environmental Protection Area to Praia do Antiguinho. To reach the beach, one can head towards Trindade-RJ and then take transport provided by the condominium to the boat boarding point.
